-- Iranian Police Detain 40 People After Deadly Mosque Bombings, AP Reports
-- Mike Harrison
-- 2010-07-17T08:07:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/iranian-police-detain-40-people-after-deadly-mosque-bombings-ap-reports.html

          
          
             Iranian police have detained 40
people in connection with two suicide bombings at a mosque in
Zahedan, the Associated Press said, citing comments made by Gen.
Ahmad Reza Radan, Iran’s deputy police chief, to the Fars news
agency.  
 The suspects “intended to create insecurity in the city of
Zahedan after the bombing,” Radan was cited as saying.  
          
          


  


        